WEBVTT

00:05.135 --> 00:08.312
So, we are back together.
[ Chuckles ]

00:09.357 --> 00:10.662
[ School bell rings ]

00:10.706 --> 00:13.056
Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:13.100 --> 00:14.492
Rome: We're gonna
walk up on the stage,

00:14.536 --> 00:17.278
and I'm gonna tell them
that my film about racism

00:17.321 --> 00:21.021
was inspired by their
poor excuse for a Dean.

00:21.064 --> 00:22.370
I know
when you were younger,

00:22.413 --> 00:24.807
I could have done a better job
of protecting you.

00:24.850 --> 00:27.244
I will never
make that mistake again.

00:27.288 --> 00:30.030
Nothing would make me happier
than us working together.

00:30.073 --> 00:32.641
Regina: I don't just want
your money. I want you.

00:32.684 --> 00:34.556
I'm not sure how much
I want to have happen.

00:34.599 --> 00:36.297
How about I just
follow your lead?

00:36.340 --> 00:39.343
I had feelings for you
when you asked me to homecoming.

00:39.387 --> 00:42.042
I just didn't realize it
at the time.

00:42.085 --> 00:43.608
Maggie: Thank you
for squeezing me in.

00:43.652 --> 00:44.696
Is everything okay?

00:44.740 --> 00:47.308
I wanted to talk
to you about

00:47.351 --> 00:48.918
me having a baby.

00:51.138 --> 00:55.403
Um, I-I was able to get pregnant
last year,

00:55.446 --> 01:00.060
uh, but the timing just wasn't
right for so many reasons.

01:00.103 --> 01:03.367
As you know, it was too close
to my chemo,

01:03.411 --> 01:05.195
and...

01:05.239 --> 01:07.197
I just wasn't ready.

01:07.241 --> 01:09.330
But now,
I'm in a different place

01:09.373 --> 01:11.201
with a different person.

01:11.245 --> 01:13.377
Um --
uh, Gary, actually.

01:13.421 --> 01:15.597
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

01:15.640 --> 01:16.815
That makes me so happy.

01:16.859 --> 01:18.643
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

01:18.687 --> 01:21.124
I was always rooting
for you two.

01:21.168 --> 01:22.908
Really? Thanks.

01:22.952 --> 01:24.649
Um, yeah.

01:24.693 --> 01:28.784
So, pregnancy is something that
I'm starting to think about,

01:28.827 --> 01:30.873
and I just --

01:30.916 --> 01:34.790
I'm here because I wanted
to know if, um...

01:34.833 --> 01:37.358
if this home
could entertain guests.

01:39.099 --> 01:42.102
Well,
the short answer is yes.

01:42.145 --> 01:44.452
Because your cancer
was estrogen negative,

01:44.495 --> 01:47.585
I'm not worried about
pregnancy-related complications.

01:47.629 --> 01:48.978
Okay.

01:49.021 --> 01:50.501
No longer radioactive.

01:50.545 --> 01:51.981
That's -- That's great.

01:52.024 --> 01:56.072
Yes, but even though you are
a healthy 30-year-old woman,

01:56.116 --> 01:58.161
with all the chemotherapy
you've been through,

01:58.205 --> 02:02.078
you may not have 10 years
of ovulatory life left.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.514
Simply put --

02:03.558 --> 02:06.038
I'm running out of time.

02:12.088 --> 02:14.699
Regina: Grande iced Americano,
soy milk,

02:14.743 --> 02:16.875
two pumps of caramel, Splenda,

02:16.919 --> 02:18.877
and an everything bagel,
lightly toasted.

02:18.921 --> 02:20.488
That sounds delicious,

02:20.531 --> 02:22.403
but I'm gonna hit
the dining hall at Sussex

02:22.446 --> 02:23.578
before we screen
our film today.

02:23.621 --> 02:25.014
I'm telling you,

02:25.057 --> 02:27.103
those prep schools have
the best tater tots.

02:27.147 --> 02:28.452
Coffee ain't for you,
playa.

02:28.496 --> 02:31.586
An order that complicated
can only mean one thing.

02:31.629 --> 02:33.022
My mom's coming over.

02:33.065 --> 02:34.241
Yeah.Oh.

02:34.284 --> 02:35.677
I have to tell her
that Dad and I

02:35.720 --> 02:37.983
are officially
in business together.

02:38.027 --> 02:40.247
You might want to take
a preemptive Advil.

02:40.290 --> 02:41.900
She practically lost her mind
when she walked in

02:41.944 --> 02:43.772
on you and Flo
cooking together,

02:43.815 --> 02:45.861
and Flo's just
my dad's girlfriend.Yeah.

02:45.904 --> 02:48.211
I had no idea your folks
hated each other that much.

02:48.255 --> 02:51.040
Oh, yeah. It's one of the main
reasons they got divorced.

02:51.083 --> 02:53.956
[ Chuckles ]It didn't help that
a few months after they split,

02:53.999 --> 02:55.349
he got together
with Angie.

02:55.392 --> 02:57.612
Which might explain
why Shelly Photoshopped

02:57.655 --> 02:59.527
the two of them out
of all of our wedding photos.

02:59.570 --> 03:00.919
Oh, that's cold.

03:00.963 --> 03:02.834
And that's why I have
to talk to her.

03:02.878 --> 03:04.662
For too long,
our family policy

03:04.706 --> 03:07.230
has been
to not discuss anything.

03:07.274 --> 03:08.753
That has to change.

03:08.797 --> 03:10.407
You know what? I don't know
what size that coffee is,

03:10.451 --> 03:12.061
but might want to make it
a venti.

03:12.104 --> 03:13.410
[ Chuckles ] Good call.

03:13.454 --> 03:14.672
[ Clicks tongue ]

03:14.716 --> 03:16.457
Alright, have fun showing
your movie.

03:16.500 --> 03:17.501
[ Smooches ]

03:17.545 --> 03:18.459
Enjoy those tater tots.

03:18.502 --> 03:19.982
Oh, you know I will.

03:20.025 --> 03:21.940
[ Door opens, closes ]

03:21.984 --> 03:24.073
Hey, read this.

03:24.116 --> 03:25.248
What is it?

03:25.292 --> 03:26.989
It's my speech
for after the screening.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.686
Dean Dennings
won't know what hit him.

03:28.730 --> 03:35.606
♪♪

03:35.650 --> 03:37.260
What's the point of a reunion,
anyway?

03:37.304 --> 03:40.263
Oh, well, um, you know,
it's an opportunity

03:40.307 --> 03:43.832
to show all your old classmates
how successful you are

03:43.875 --> 03:45.268
and rub it
in their faces.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.617
[ Chuckles ]

03:46.661 --> 03:48.750
So, somewhere around 2050,

03:48.793 --> 03:50.360
I get to brag
to Tommy Johnson

03:50.404 --> 03:52.232
about being the first surgeon
on the moon?

03:52.275 --> 03:54.059
Exactly.

03:54.103 --> 03:55.452
And I think
that astronaut doctors

03:55.496 --> 03:56.932
have to know
their fractions,

03:56.975 --> 03:59.195
so get cracking
on that homework.

03:59.239 --> 04:02.242
Joo Hee: Come on, Theo.
Breakfast is ready.

04:04.809 --> 04:08.683
You know, Randy Kwan's mother
say he'll be at reunion.

04:08.726 --> 04:12.904
Mom, I barely knew Randy
in high school.

04:15.951 --> 04:19.563
Besides, Greta and I have
a-a bunch of people

04:19.607 --> 04:20.999
we want to catch up with.

04:21.043 --> 04:22.218
Greta Strobe?

04:22.262 --> 04:23.219
Mm-hmm.

04:23.263 --> 04:25.439
[ Speaking Korean ]

04:29.094 --> 04:31.749
No, Molly McCabe
was a troublemaker.

04:31.793 --> 04:34.143
She almost got expelled
like five times.

04:34.186 --> 04:38.060
Greta happens to be a very
in-demand tattoo artist.

04:38.103 --> 04:43.587
I don't understand why someone
would ruin their body like that.

04:43.631 --> 04:45.241
[ Sighs ]

04:45.285 --> 04:54.076
♪♪

04:54.119 --> 04:55.904
Gary: Dan, what happened?
Where's Colin?

04:55.947 --> 04:57.340
You brought home
the wrong dog!

04:57.384 --> 04:58.863
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, right.

04:58.907 --> 05:00.604
You are not
getting me today.

05:00.648 --> 05:03.477
Seriously? You two are
still playing Made-Ya-Look?

05:03.520 --> 05:05.217
I thought you just did that
with Theo,

05:05.261 --> 05:07.176
when Eddie said he wasn't
allowed any more screen time.

05:07.219 --> 05:08.438
Yeah,
that's how it started.

05:08.482 --> 05:09.961
Then I got Maggie,
again...

05:10.005 --> 05:11.223
Mm-hmm....and again.

05:11.267 --> 05:13.356
And now she's taking it
to another level.

05:13.400 --> 05:16.054
Yeah, I may have convinced
his barber to make him look

05:16.098 --> 05:17.926
in the mirror
after his haircut.

05:17.969 --> 05:20.798
Trust between a man and his
barber should never be broken.

05:20.842 --> 05:21.930
He shaves the back of my neck
with a blade

05:21.973 --> 05:23.540
that could decapitate me.

05:23.584 --> 05:26.151
Well, then you're lucky all
I had him do is make you look.

05:26.195 --> 05:28.371
You know, it really concerns me
that two

05:28.415 --> 05:30.417
of the most important adults
in my life

05:30.460 --> 05:32.201
have nothing better to do
with their time

05:32.244 --> 05:34.943
than to play a game
intended for children.

05:34.986 --> 05:37.467
That's a loser's mindset,
Dan.

05:37.511 --> 05:39.817
It's like Maggie said, it's all
about getting the other person

05:39.861 --> 05:42.124
to drop their guard
so that you can --

05:42.167 --> 05:43.386
Hey.

05:43.430 --> 05:44.561
Is that a hickey?

05:44.605 --> 05:46.520
Nice try, Mendez.

05:46.563 --> 05:48.391
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

05:48.435 --> 05:51.438
Oh, hi, Cam.
How are you?

05:51.481 --> 05:52.700
Made ya look.

05:52.743 --> 05:55.180
It's just too easy.

05:55.224 --> 05:56.268
Hello?

05:56.312 --> 05:59.271
Yo.
Where are you rushing off to?

05:59.315 --> 06:01.143
I want to get in an ab workout
before Milo and I go

06:01.186 --> 06:02.536
to our friend
Sarah's party,

06:02.579 --> 06:04.799
which I still need
a ride to.

06:04.842 --> 06:05.974
Yeah,
you know the deal.

06:06.017 --> 06:07.323
First you gotta walk Colin
six blocks.

06:07.367 --> 06:08.411
I did.

06:08.455 --> 06:11.283
Really?

06:11.327 --> 06:13.764
You sure you wanna stick
to that?

06:13.808 --> 06:16.245
Because I put this locator
on his collar

06:16.288 --> 06:18.595
after he got out
last time,

06:18.639 --> 06:21.555
which means I just tracked
the whole half a block

06:21.598 --> 06:23.034
that you walked him.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.775
I'll still give you a ride
to the party,

06:24.819 --> 06:27.430
but if he takes a dump
on that rug,

06:27.474 --> 06:28.518
you're cleaning it up.

06:28.562 --> 06:29.954
Deal.

06:29.998 --> 06:32.392
Do you wanna join me
for the ab workout?

06:32.435 --> 06:35.003
I'd rather babysit
Darcy's new kid.

06:35.046 --> 06:36.657
By the way,
she had the kid.

06:36.700 --> 06:37.919
Awesome.

06:37.962 --> 06:39.964
♪♪

06:40.008 --> 06:43.011
"The fact that Sussex promoted
a man like Dean Dennings,

06:43.054 --> 06:46.188
who turned a blind eye to such
an egregious racist incident

06:46.231 --> 06:48.146
just confirms
this institution stands

06:48.190 --> 06:51.193
on a foundation
of revisionist history."

06:51.236 --> 06:53.021
Damn. I thought you just wanted
to call him out,

06:53.064 --> 06:55.110
not burn
the whole place down.

06:55.153 --> 06:56.807
When I found that "Whites Only"
sign on the water fountain,

06:56.851 --> 06:58.896
I went to that man
for help.

06:58.940 --> 07:02.552
He told me to forget about it,
"just let it go."

07:02.596 --> 07:04.641
And the mere fact
that he's still at Sussex

07:04.685 --> 07:07.165
all these years later
needs to be addressed.

07:07.209 --> 07:08.819
'Cause until it is,
it's not just about Dennings.

07:08.863 --> 07:10.473
It's about
the entire institution.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.257
Look, I get it.

07:12.301 --> 07:13.824
I'm all for speaking truth
to power,

07:13.868 --> 07:16.305
but have you thought
about your friend, Dre,

07:16.348 --> 07:19.003
and what it could do to
the Black students who go there?

07:19.047 --> 07:20.962
I'm doing this
for those kids.

07:21.005 --> 07:22.659
And the kids who came before me
and after me

07:22.703 --> 07:23.660
that went through the same thing
that I went through

07:23.704 --> 07:25.532
with this place.

07:25.575 --> 07:26.750
It's the right thing
to do.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.450
And is that why you didn't
mention it to Gina?

07:30.493 --> 07:31.886
I didn't mention it to Gina
'cause I don't need

07:31.929 --> 07:34.628
people questioning me
like you are right now.

07:34.671 --> 07:36.760
I'm not saying this because
I'm worried about Dennings.

07:36.804 --> 07:37.848
I'm not even worried
about the school.

07:37.892 --> 07:39.284
I'm worried about you.

07:41.548 --> 07:44.768
You've been going through
a lot lately,

07:44.812 --> 07:47.554
and I don't know
that this is gonna help.

07:47.597 --> 07:49.338
Oh, so you're saying forget
about it,

07:49.381 --> 07:51.993
"Just --
Just let it go."

07:52.036 --> 07:53.821
No,
that's not what I'm saying.

07:53.864 --> 07:56.214
Good. Because we leave
in a half-hour.

07:56.258 --> 08:03.221
♪♪

08:03.265 --> 08:05.310
Gary: Oh, there he is!

08:05.354 --> 08:07.225
Still wearing the clothes
he had on yesterday,

08:07.269 --> 08:09.271
doing the roll of shame.

08:09.314 --> 08:11.403
I take it you and Anna
had quite the night.

08:11.447 --> 08:13.580
You got me.
[ Chuckles ]

08:13.623 --> 08:15.016
I'm gonna go
sleep it off.

08:15.059 --> 08:16.800
That's my boy.

08:16.844 --> 08:17.845
Proud of you, man.

08:17.888 --> 08:19.499
Eddie:
You're making it weird.

08:21.370 --> 08:22.458
And where are you going?

08:22.502 --> 08:24.068
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, like I'm telling you.

08:24.112 --> 08:27.376
You are not gonna Make-Me-Look
out in the wild.

08:27.419 --> 08:29.596
Wow.

08:29.639 --> 08:32.512
She's just too smart for us,
Colin.

08:32.555 --> 08:34.862
[ Sighs ]

08:34.905 --> 08:36.733
Mm.

08:36.777 --> 08:38.605
That's my Bloom.

08:38.648 --> 08:40.694
Always one step ahead.

08:40.737 --> 08:41.999
Always.

08:45.525 --> 08:46.787
Oh, honey, I love this.

08:46.830 --> 08:48.310
Right?
At first, I was skeptical,

08:48.353 --> 08:50.486
but this truck
has everything I need.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.314
And the best part is it keeps
my overhead down,

08:52.357 --> 08:54.098
so I won't be struggling
to cover the rent every month

08:54.142 --> 08:55.404
like I did at Someday.

08:55.447 --> 08:57.406
Don't be fooled
if you think this is gonna be

08:57.449 --> 08:59.277
less work than Someday.

08:59.321 --> 09:01.584
You are gonna need
more help.

09:01.628 --> 09:02.890
Right.

09:04.195 --> 09:07.111
So, uh, Mom...

09:07.155 --> 09:09.461
that's not all I wanted
to talk to you about.

09:11.246 --> 09:15.337
Uh, when I was down in Miami,
I, uh...

09:15.380 --> 09:17.295
I saw Dad.
Oh.

09:17.339 --> 09:20.908
And he actually found time
for you between rounds of golf?

09:20.951 --> 09:22.083
Sorry.

09:22.126 --> 09:24.085
How are he and Angie?

09:24.128 --> 09:28.393
Actually,
Angie left him.

09:28.437 --> 09:29.786
What?

09:29.830 --> 09:30.874
Yeah.

09:30.918 --> 09:33.224
And I think
it's really changed him.

09:33.268 --> 09:34.835
[ Scoffs ][ Knock on door ]

09:34.878 --> 09:36.532
I'll believe that
when I see it.

09:37.925 --> 09:39.927
[ Door opens ]Ronald: Hey, baby. I know
we're supposed to meet later,

09:39.970 --> 09:41.798
but my graphics guy sent over
the artwork,

09:41.842 --> 09:42.625
couldn't wait
to share it with you.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.409
Regina: Oh, Dad --

09:44.453 --> 09:45.933
Shelly.

09:45.976 --> 09:49.110
Artwork?
What's he talking about?

09:49.153 --> 09:51.678
Well, I-I was about to --We're going into business
together.

09:53.201 --> 09:54.202
Oh.

09:54.245 --> 09:55.551
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

09:55.595 --> 09:57.640
So, that's what
this is all about.

09:57.684 --> 10:01.775
The out-of-the-blue invitation,
the everything bagel,

10:01.818 --> 10:04.473
the coffee
that was almostperfect.

10:04.516 --> 10:05.866
You were
sweetening me up.

10:05.909 --> 10:08.346
You thought I'd be upset
about you working with him,

10:08.390 --> 10:11.480
and I have to say...

10:11.523 --> 10:13.917
I'm thrilled.

10:13.961 --> 10:14.918
Wait, what?

10:14.962 --> 10:16.833
I'm glad
you two are doing this.

10:16.877 --> 10:19.009
I couldn't be happier.

10:19.053 --> 10:22.578
Now, let's go see
this food truck.

10:22.622 --> 10:26.016
[ Chuckles ]

10:26.060 --> 10:27.670
Um...

10:27.714 --> 10:29.716
[ Door opens ]

10:29.759 --> 10:33.023
♪♪

10:37.288 --> 10:39.247
[ Inhales deeply ]

10:39.290 --> 10:42.250
God, it smells exactly like
it did 25 years ago.

10:42.293 --> 10:44.687
Like B.O.
and desperation.

10:44.731 --> 10:46.123
Some things never change.

10:46.167 --> 10:48.604
Yeah. Like your mom giving me
the stink eye.

10:48.648 --> 10:51.346
I'm really sorry
about that.

10:51.389 --> 10:53.609
Don't be.
I have been scandalizing parents

10:53.653 --> 10:54.828
since the late '90s.

10:54.871 --> 10:56.699
[ Chuckles ]

10:56.743 --> 11:00.050
You know, I-I do plan
to tell her about me.

11:00.094 --> 11:02.139
And us.

11:02.183 --> 11:04.359
I'm just...
working up to it.

11:04.402 --> 11:06.709
[ Chuckles ]

11:06.753 --> 11:08.319
Hey, believe me,
I get it.

11:08.363 --> 11:11.888
It took me a long time to work
up the nerve to tell my family.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.716
You should take as much time
as you need.

11:13.760 --> 11:15.805
Thank you.

11:15.849 --> 11:17.328
Now let's go see
if the cafeteria

11:17.372 --> 11:19.200
still smells like
Teen Spirit.

11:19.243 --> 11:22.986
♪♪

11:23.030 --> 11:25.989
Dude, looks like
she's headed to Longwood.

11:26.033 --> 11:27.774
Probably that big Target,
right?

11:27.817 --> 11:30.167
I can see it now -- Maggie's
just going about her day.

11:30.211 --> 11:31.342
"Ooh, what's that?
Oh, that looks cool."

11:31.386 --> 11:32.822
And then -- bam!

11:32.866 --> 11:34.694
Runs into a mannequin
holding this.

11:34.737 --> 11:35.738
That's cool.

11:35.782 --> 11:37.348
Yeah.
After you kidnap her,

11:37.392 --> 11:39.742
throw her in your van,
can I get her apartment

11:39.786 --> 11:41.135
so I don't have
to live with you anymore?

11:41.178 --> 11:42.919
Wow.

11:42.963 --> 11:44.704
Mean humor
doesn't usually work for you,

11:44.747 --> 11:46.749
but that was
genuinely funny.

11:46.793 --> 11:49.447
What's going on, Ed?

11:49.491 --> 11:50.361
[ Sighs ]

11:50.405 --> 11:51.841
I-It's nothing.

11:54.017 --> 11:55.584
Something happen
with Anna?

11:55.627 --> 11:57.804
It's more like
what didn't happen.

11:59.806 --> 12:01.764
Let's just say

12:01.808 --> 12:05.246
that the train pulled
out of the station last night,

12:05.289 --> 12:08.162
but wasn't able
to reach its destination.

12:08.205 --> 12:09.685
Ah.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.208
Train arrived early,
huh?

12:11.252 --> 12:12.775
No.

12:12.819 --> 12:15.778
It didn't make it
to the station at all.

12:15.822 --> 12:17.301
You just said
it left the station.

12:17.345 --> 12:18.389
The first station.

12:18.433 --> 12:19.695
Wait,
there's two stations?

12:19.739 --> 12:21.044
No wonder the train
pulled out early.

12:21.088 --> 12:23.873
No,
the train didn't --

12:23.917 --> 12:25.179
[ Inhales sharply ]

12:25.222 --> 12:27.790
I couldn't finish, okay?

12:27.834 --> 12:29.052
Neither could she.

12:29.096 --> 12:31.098
Ah.

12:31.141 --> 12:33.056
You know,
just when I think

12:33.100 --> 12:36.756
I have finally adjusted
to my situation...

12:36.799 --> 12:38.322
Did you talk
to your doctor?

12:38.366 --> 12:41.282
After the accident,
she prescribed me...

12:41.325 --> 12:42.457
you know...

12:42.500 --> 12:44.024
Yeah.

12:44.067 --> 12:46.722
But I never needed them
with Katherine.

12:46.766 --> 12:48.115
And last night,
by the time I realized

12:48.158 --> 12:52.423
I...needed
a little extra staying power,

12:52.467 --> 12:54.599
it was too late.

12:54.643 --> 12:57.820
How'd you leave things with her
this morning?

12:57.864 --> 12:59.517
We had a lot
of awkward conversation

12:59.561 --> 13:01.345
over frozen waffles.

13:01.389 --> 13:02.869
Then I left.

13:02.912 --> 13:05.828
We're supposed to go to
a concert tonight, but now...

13:05.872 --> 13:07.090
I don't even know.

13:07.134 --> 13:08.875
Alright,
in my experience --

13:08.918 --> 13:11.399
which, as you know,
is vast --

13:11.442 --> 13:14.097
I find that honesty
is a hell of an aphrodisiac.

13:14.141 --> 13:17.318
So, why won't you talk to her,
huh,

13:17.361 --> 13:19.624
take one of your little pills,
see what happens?

13:19.668 --> 13:21.844
I bet you'll be pitching a tent
just in time

13:21.888 --> 13:23.193
for The J. Geils Band.

13:23.237 --> 13:24.847
And he's back.

13:24.891 --> 13:27.023
[ Chuckles ]
Much like The J. Geils Band,

13:27.067 --> 13:28.111
I never left.

13:30.157 --> 13:32.594
Seriously, thank you.

13:32.637 --> 13:35.945
It is nice to be able to have a
mature conversation about this.

13:35.989 --> 13:38.513
Well, I am the epitome
of maturity.

13:38.556 --> 13:39.862
Ooh!
Maggie's parking!

13:39.906 --> 13:41.429
Okay. Alright.

13:41.472 --> 13:43.126
I gotta go beat my girlfriend
at Made-Ya-Look.

13:43.170 --> 13:45.389
[ Chuckles ]

13:45.433 --> 13:48.479
♪♪

13:48.523 --> 13:49.785
Wow.

13:49.829 --> 13:51.482
It's a pretty good
turnout.

13:51.526 --> 13:53.180
Yeah.

13:53.223 --> 13:56.487
Hi.Woman: Hi. Welcome.

13:56.531 --> 13:58.576
Oh, my God.

13:58.620 --> 14:01.666
♪♪

14:01.710 --> 14:04.539
Wow. Someone grew up
and got their braces off.

14:04.582 --> 14:05.801
[ Exhales sharply ]

14:07.934 --> 14:10.458
I'm just saying, it's not
too late to change the speech.

14:10.501 --> 14:13.156
Yeah, are you saying that
because it's what you believe,

14:13.200 --> 14:14.157
or 'cause you just want
to be able to come back

14:14.201 --> 14:16.116
and get more tater tots?

14:16.159 --> 14:17.247
Why can't it be both?

14:17.291 --> 14:19.684
Rome. Tyrell.

14:19.728 --> 14:22.600
Hey, man. Thank you, guys,
for doing this.

14:22.644 --> 14:24.298
Our kids are really looking
forward to seeing the film.

14:24.341 --> 14:26.213
Man, we appreciate you
setting this up.

14:26.256 --> 14:27.736
Hey, Mr. Washington.

14:27.779 --> 14:30.870
Kendra, this is Mr. Howard.
This is Tyrell.

14:30.913 --> 14:32.872
Kendra will be
introducing you.

14:32.915 --> 14:34.917
Kendra: Hi.Student: Hi, Dean Dennings.

14:34.961 --> 14:36.832
Rome Howard.

14:36.876 --> 14:40.444
It's not every day we get
a big-time Hollywood director

14:40.488 --> 14:41.924
on campus.

14:41.968 --> 14:43.491
Can we get a few pictures?Man: Of course. You got it.

14:43.534 --> 14:47.277
You are a great example
of what a Sussex Prep education

14:47.321 --> 14:48.713
can make happen.[ Camera shutter clicks ]

14:48.757 --> 14:51.194
Which is why we are going
to be featuring you

14:51.238 --> 14:54.328
on the school's website
during Black History Month.

14:54.371 --> 14:56.286
Our donors love
this kinda stuff.

14:56.330 --> 14:57.809
Let's go see the movie.

14:57.853 --> 15:04.468
♪♪

15:04.512 --> 15:07.776
Forget everything I said.
You need to take that guy down.

15:07.819 --> 15:12.650
♪♪

15:17.264 --> 15:24.662
♪♪

15:24.706 --> 15:26.229
Rome.

15:26.273 --> 15:28.188
Look, I wanna apologize
for that.

15:28.231 --> 15:29.798
I hope you know
I didn't invite you here

15:29.841 --> 15:32.105
to get more donations.

15:32.148 --> 15:33.628
How do you come to work
every day

15:33.671 --> 15:35.891
knowing that guy's
your boss?

15:35.935 --> 15:38.067
Look, man,
the fact is

15:38.111 --> 15:40.722
these places are full of guys
like Dennings.

15:40.765 --> 15:42.854
They're what's left of
institutions that are changing.

15:42.898 --> 15:44.987
You keep saying this place
is changing,

15:45.031 --> 15:46.946
but I don't see it.

15:46.989 --> 15:48.904
And you apologizing for him
is part of the problem.

15:51.124 --> 15:54.257
These kids deserve to know
the truth about this place,

15:54.301 --> 15:56.607
and as soon as this movie's
over, I'm gonna tell them.

15:59.610 --> 16:01.569
You know, I-I guess we both
came back to Sussex

16:01.612 --> 16:04.006
with an axe to grind.

16:04.050 --> 16:05.703
I'm using mine to chop down
the things

16:05.747 --> 16:08.532
that are standing
in the way of progress.

16:08.576 --> 16:11.187
You get to decide
how to use yours.

16:11.231 --> 16:14.669
Just make sure you're
not chopping down so much

16:14.712 --> 16:16.366
that there's nothing left.

16:16.410 --> 16:21.589
♪♪

16:21.632 --> 16:27.029
♪♪

16:27.073 --> 16:28.988
Alright, it's gotta be
one of these two.

16:29.031 --> 16:29.989
Hey, Shell?

16:30.032 --> 16:31.425
Yeah?Hit it.

16:31.468 --> 16:32.774
Okay.

16:34.602 --> 16:36.778
[ Engine starts ]

16:36.821 --> 16:37.997
Whoo!

16:38.040 --> 16:39.433
Oh, that sounds
a lot better.

16:39.476 --> 16:40.782
Knew I could fix it.

16:40.825 --> 16:41.870
Ho!

16:41.913 --> 16:44.090
You mean,
"we" could fix it.

16:44.133 --> 16:45.700
We could fix it.
You're right.

16:45.743 --> 16:47.528
We are still
a pretty good team.

16:48.833 --> 16:50.139
Remember when we "fixed"
the shocks

16:50.183 --> 16:52.794
in the Buick we had
back in '79?

16:52.837 --> 16:55.710
[ Chuckles ]

16:55.753 --> 16:59.018
You remember why they went bad
in the first place?

16:59.061 --> 17:00.628
Mm.
I plead the fifth on that one.

17:00.671 --> 17:02.891
[ Both laugh ]

17:05.198 --> 17:06.199
Are you alright, sweetie?

17:06.242 --> 17:08.114
Hmm? Mm-hmm.

17:08.157 --> 17:11.508
Yeah. Honestly, I am glad
you're so okay with this.

17:11.552 --> 17:14.076
Of course I am.

17:14.120 --> 17:18.124
I'm glad your dad's here,
finally helping you.

17:18.167 --> 17:19.777
Whoa. W-What's that
supposed to mean?

17:19.821 --> 17:21.910
I always helped out
as best I could.

17:21.953 --> 17:24.956
Yeah.
From a thousand miles away.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.523
Almost as if
you were trying

17:26.567 --> 17:28.786
to get as far away from us
as possible.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.701
Well, we both know
it wasn't Regina

17:30.745 --> 17:32.268
that I had a problem
with.

17:32.312 --> 17:33.487
Mom. Hi.

17:33.530 --> 17:35.576
Why don't I just show you
the deep fryer?

17:35.619 --> 17:37.578
No, no, no, no, no.
No, no, no.

17:37.621 --> 17:39.754
Real mature, Ron.

17:39.797 --> 17:42.800
[ Sighs ]Can't imagine why things didn't
work out between you and Ange.

17:42.844 --> 17:44.237
Shelly,
please, uh, remind me --

17:44.280 --> 17:46.543
when is the last time
you had a relationship?

17:46.587 --> 17:47.544
-Okay.
-Oh s--

17:47.588 --> 17:49.720
Hey, hey, Mom, Dad, stop.

17:49.764 --> 17:51.070
You know what?

17:51.113 --> 17:52.114
I shouldn't have come.

17:52.158 --> 17:54.203
I'm just gonna get my things
and go.

17:54.247 --> 17:55.770
Mom.

17:57.902 --> 17:59.774
[ Sighs ]

17:59.817 --> 18:03.082
♪ Everywhere I go,
people stop and they see ♪

18:03.125 --> 18:05.954
So, Katherine,
I knew you would be here.

18:05.997 --> 18:08.522
In fact, my mom texted me
three times today already.

18:08.565 --> 18:10.045
Oh, I know.
My mom's already

18:10.089 --> 18:12.003
registering us
at Bed Bath & Beyond.

18:12.047 --> 18:13.353
[ Chuckles ]

18:13.396 --> 18:15.920
Yeah. It's weird
to be back here, huh?

18:15.964 --> 18:18.184
Oh, after the number of times
I got caught smoking pot

18:18.227 --> 18:20.055
in the
activities hall bathroom,

18:20.099 --> 18:21.839
I was surprised
they let me in.[ Chuckles ]

18:21.883 --> 18:24.190
You, uh, wouldn't happen to have
any on you, would you?

18:24.233 --> 18:25.930
Randy Kwan.

18:25.974 --> 18:26.931
I didn't know
you had it in you.

18:26.975 --> 18:28.977
Oh, I definitely have it
in me.

18:29.020 --> 18:31.153
Just ask this one. Greta was at
all my high school parties.

18:31.197 --> 18:33.373
Yes, that's where some of
my favorite memories were made.

18:33.416 --> 18:36.115
Do you remember when we went
pool hopping that one Halloween?

18:36.158 --> 18:37.246
How could I forget?

18:37.290 --> 18:38.900
I had my first kiss
with Molly McCabe

18:38.943 --> 18:40.510
running between my pool
and Paul Mastriani's.

18:40.554 --> 18:42.904
[ Chuckles ]Whatever happened
to Molly McCabe?

18:42.947 --> 18:44.427
Oh, you're not gonna
believe this,

18:44.471 --> 18:47.169
but she is a super successful
hedge fund manager now.

18:47.213 --> 18:50.259
Huh.Molly McCabe manages
a hedge fund?

18:50.303 --> 18:52.348
The girl who put laxatives
in the principal's coffee?

18:52.392 --> 18:54.176
Uh -- uh, allegedly.

18:54.220 --> 18:55.830
[ Chuckles ] High school her
would be so disappointed

18:55.873 --> 18:57.701
she turned out
to be such a square.

18:57.745 --> 18:59.703
Oh, well, that's probably true
for all of us.

18:59.747 --> 19:03.185
Remind me, Randy --
How many different "Amys"

19:03.229 --> 19:05.144
did you hook up with
at your big post-prom party?

19:05.187 --> 19:06.971
[ Snorts ] Shh, shh, there's,
like, two of them here, okay?

19:07.015 --> 19:08.147
So...

19:08.190 --> 19:09.539
You were there, right,
Katherine?

19:09.583 --> 19:12.238
Uh...no, I-I think
I missed that one.

19:12.281 --> 19:14.327
Ah, well,
consider yourself lucky.

19:14.370 --> 19:16.459
Mastriani puked all over
my Air Jordan collection.

19:16.503 --> 19:19.027
Oh, my God.
I totally remember that.

19:19.070 --> 19:21.508
Yeah, you still wore those,
like, the rest of senior year.

19:21.551 --> 19:23.423
[ Chuckles ]
God, I miss high school.

19:23.466 --> 19:26.252
I'm gonna get a drink.Is that Paul Mastriani
right there?

19:26.295 --> 19:28.428
Is he wearing Air Jordans?

19:28.471 --> 19:30.386
That's deliberate. He's --
He's messing with me, right?[ Laughs ]

19:30.430 --> 19:37.828
♪♪

19:37.872 --> 19:45.271
♪♪

19:45.314 --> 19:47.621
Your driver has arrived.

19:47.664 --> 19:49.013
Where's Gary?

19:49.057 --> 19:52.321
He is busy playing peek-a-boo
with Maggie,

19:52.365 --> 19:53.540
so you're stuck with me.

19:53.583 --> 19:55.672
The good news is
I'm a five-star driver.

19:55.716 --> 19:58.893
Uh...yeah,
I-I can't go anymore.

19:58.936 --> 20:00.895
Turns out
it's a pool party,

20:00.938 --> 20:03.245
and I didn't think
to pack my swimsuit.

20:03.289 --> 20:05.334
Oh.
We can hook you up.

20:05.378 --> 20:06.944
I know for a fact that Gary
kept a few Speedos

20:06.988 --> 20:08.163
from his "Borat" phase.

20:08.207 --> 20:09.469
[ As Borat ] High five!

20:12.907 --> 20:15.301
[ Normal voice ] I'm sure he has
some regular trunks, too.

20:15.344 --> 20:17.955
Don't worry about it.
I'm not going.

20:17.999 --> 20:24.005
♪♪

20:24.048 --> 20:26.616
I also think we should put
our name here.

20:26.660 --> 20:29.619
That way, anyone stuck behind us
in traffic will remember.

20:29.663 --> 20:31.099
Great idea.

20:33.710 --> 20:37.845
Gigi, I'm sorry things got tense
with your mother.

20:41.805 --> 20:43.024
I should've kept
my mouth shut.

20:43.067 --> 20:45.244
Yeah.

20:45.287 --> 20:48.203
I just wish you could be
a little more patient.

20:48.247 --> 20:51.685
You being back here is --
it's a lot for her.

20:51.728 --> 20:53.382
Is it?

20:53.426 --> 20:55.950
Dad, you left and replaced her
with another woman.

20:55.993 --> 20:56.951
Is that
what she told you?

20:56.994 --> 20:59.083
No,
she didn't have to.

20:59.127 --> 21:01.999
You were with Angie less than
a year after leaving Mom.

21:02.043 --> 21:03.610
It's not hard
to do the math.

21:03.653 --> 21:05.176
Alright, first of all,

21:05.220 --> 21:08.223
I didn't even meet Angie until
after your mom and I split up.

21:08.267 --> 21:09.833
And I left because...

21:11.661 --> 21:13.794
Because what?

21:13.837 --> 21:15.839
I'm not having
this conversation.

21:15.883 --> 21:17.493
I didn't want
to hurt the relationship

21:17.537 --> 21:20.540
with your mother then...

21:20.583 --> 21:22.455
and I don't want
to do it now.

21:22.498 --> 21:23.760
Dad.

21:23.804 --> 21:25.762
Please.

21:25.806 --> 21:27.547
Tell me the truth.

21:30.158 --> 21:31.638
The truth?
Yeah.

21:31.681 --> 21:35.468
♪♪

21:35.511 --> 21:38.514
The truth is I left because your
mother was having an affair.

21:38.558 --> 21:41.822
♪♪

21:50.526 --> 21:52.093
We need to talk.

21:52.136 --> 21:53.964
I know.

21:54.008 --> 21:55.531
I'm sorry I let your father
get to me.

21:55.575 --> 21:58.229
It's just -- There's a reason
why we haven't spoken

21:58.273 --> 21:59.579
all these years.

21:59.622 --> 22:01.363
Does it have anything to do
with your affair?

22:04.410 --> 22:05.759
Dad told me.

22:08.457 --> 22:11.852
You let me believe
my whole life

22:11.895 --> 22:14.898
that Dad left us,
that he was the bad guy.

22:14.942 --> 22:17.379
No.
I never said that.

22:17.423 --> 22:20.339
Maybe not, but you implied it
with your attitude

22:20.382 --> 22:21.949
every time his name
came up,

22:21.992 --> 22:24.778
and all the while, you were
the one who was unfaithful.

22:24.821 --> 22:26.519
Regina, it's not true.

22:26.562 --> 22:28.172
I never cheated.

22:28.216 --> 22:30.653
It's just what
I let your father believe.

22:30.697 --> 22:32.568
What? Why?

22:32.612 --> 22:36.180
Because at a certain point
in our marriage,

22:36.224 --> 22:41.011
something changed
with our...

22:41.055 --> 22:43.536
physical relationship.

22:43.579 --> 22:47.670
I-I stopped wanting
to be intimate,

22:47.714 --> 22:50.194
and at the time,

22:50.238 --> 22:52.675
I didn't --

22:52.719 --> 22:54.416
I didn't understand
what was going on.

22:54.460 --> 22:55.852
But with lots of therapy,

22:55.896 --> 22:57.854
it finally made sense.

23:01.510 --> 23:06.776
When you were, I don't know,
about five,

23:06.820 --> 23:09.475
uh, my brother,
he moved back to Boston.

23:09.518 --> 23:13.000
And his presence
and seeing him regularly

23:13.043 --> 23:14.480
just -- it just...

23:16.960 --> 23:18.135
Of course, I --

23:21.182 --> 23:23.184
I didn't put
the two things together.

23:23.227 --> 23:26.579
I-I just know that --
that after he came back,

23:26.622 --> 23:31.540
the -- the thought of having sex
with anyone

23:31.584 --> 23:34.021
made me physically ill.

23:34.064 --> 23:37.459
And the more your father
tried to figure it out,

23:37.503 --> 23:42.986
about what was going on,
the more I felt trapped.

23:43.030 --> 23:47.730
And I-I-I had no idea
how to talk about it.

23:47.774 --> 23:50.864
And then,
one morning after church,

23:50.907 --> 23:53.475
he saw me laughing
with Frank Harris.

23:53.519 --> 23:55.390
The choir director?

23:55.434 --> 23:59.525
And I hadn't laughed like that
with your father in ages,

23:59.568 --> 24:03.659
and he got the wrong idea.

24:03.703 --> 24:05.574
And that night, he --

24:05.618 --> 24:09.012
he asked me
if I was having an affair.

24:09.056 --> 24:12.276
And -- And you just went
with it?

24:12.320 --> 24:15.715
Honey, you have to understand,
we were just so unhappy.

24:15.758 --> 24:17.107
And we were fighting
every day,

24:17.151 --> 24:20.415
and I just figured that
it was only a matter of time

24:20.459 --> 24:23.810
before he left me
for someone else.

24:23.853 --> 24:25.072
Oh.

24:25.115 --> 24:27.378
[ Sniffles ]
I am so sorry, baby.

24:27.422 --> 24:28.945
It's not your fault.

24:30.599 --> 24:32.035
[ Exhales sharply ]

24:33.733 --> 24:34.864
But you know what, Mom?

24:34.908 --> 24:36.736
It's not Dad's fault,
either.

24:36.779 --> 24:39.652
I made such a mess
of it,

24:39.695 --> 24:45.222
and I wish I could tell him
the truth about...all of it.

24:45.266 --> 24:47.311
We'll do it together.

24:47.355 --> 24:48.965
Oh.

24:49.009 --> 24:50.576
I love you.

24:50.619 --> 24:52.752
I love you, too.

24:52.795 --> 24:54.928
[ Sniffles ]
It's gonna be okay.

24:56.973 --> 24:58.192
[ Chuckles ]

24:58.235 --> 25:00.368
Got you now, Bloom.

25:00.411 --> 25:01.935
[ Sighs ]

25:01.978 --> 25:04.154
You can run,
but you can't hide.

25:04.198 --> 25:08.637
♪♪

25:08.681 --> 25:10.987
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

25:11.031 --> 25:14.948
♪♪

25:14.991 --> 25:16.253
Hey-yo?

25:16.297 --> 25:18.038
Hey, do you know
what's going on with Danny?

25:18.081 --> 25:19.953
He just made up
the flimsiest excuse

25:19.996 --> 25:21.520
to bail
on his friend's party.

25:21.563 --> 25:22.825
What do I do?

25:22.869 --> 25:24.523
Look, Ed, I gotta call you back,
a'ight?

25:24.566 --> 25:26.655
I'm -- I'm kinda busy.

25:26.699 --> 25:29.832
Can you focus on something
other than surprising

25:29.876 --> 25:32.748
your girlfriend
playing that dumb game?

25:32.792 --> 25:35.577
Yeah, well, it turns out
the surprise is on me.

25:35.621 --> 25:38.319
Maggie's
at a fertility clinic.

25:40.190 --> 25:41.496
That's great.

25:41.540 --> 25:43.019
Is it?

25:43.063 --> 25:45.239
I thought I wanted
to be a dad,

25:45.282 --> 25:49.765
but all the stuff
that happened with Sophie --

25:49.809 --> 25:52.289
what if I'm
just terrible at it?

25:52.333 --> 25:55.423
Maybe that's why Maggie didn't
tell me where she was going.

25:55.466 --> 25:56.729
For all I know,
she's here to find out

25:56.772 --> 25:58.382
about getting
her tubes tied.

25:58.426 --> 26:00.471
Okay,
now you're spiraling.

26:00.515 --> 26:04.084
I, an actual father,
am calling you

26:04.127 --> 26:05.781
to get advice about
how to talk to Danny.

26:05.825 --> 26:08.175
Theo is an open book
compared to him.

26:08.218 --> 26:11.091
Dan's easy. Just challenge him
to whatever video game's

26:11.134 --> 26:13.049
still in the console, and by
the end of the first level,

26:13.093 --> 26:15.269
he'll let his guard down
and start talking.

26:15.312 --> 26:17.358
And you're seriously worried
about your dad skills?

26:19.142 --> 26:21.536
Come on, man.
You got this.

26:21.580 --> 26:31.372
♪♪

26:31.415 --> 26:40.903
♪♪

26:40.947 --> 26:42.470
Gary,
what are you doing here?

26:42.513 --> 26:44.733
I, uh...

26:44.777 --> 26:46.735
[ Chuckles ]

26:46.779 --> 26:48.781
...was, uh,
trying to...

26:48.824 --> 26:50.130
Make-You-Look.

26:51.610 --> 26:56.615
And I-I realize now
that, um, this --

26:56.658 --> 27:00.401
excuse me -- might have been
a bit of an overstep.

27:00.444 --> 27:03.883
So, I can hit the road
right now,

27:03.926 --> 27:05.711
if that's what you want.
Just say the word.

27:07.147 --> 27:08.888
[ Sighs ]

27:08.931 --> 27:10.716
[ Pats couch ]

27:14.284 --> 27:16.896
[ Sighs ]

27:16.939 --> 27:19.028
So, I went to go see
my oncologist.

27:19.072 --> 27:20.856
What?
No, everything's okay.

27:20.900 --> 27:22.945
With that.
He just got in my head

27:22.989 --> 27:28.385
about how much "ovulatory life"
I have left after all the chemo.

27:28.429 --> 27:31.040
And I know how much you want
to start a family eventually,

27:31.084 --> 27:34.914
and I think
I want that someday, too.

27:34.957 --> 27:40.049
So, I'm just here to find out
if we have the green light.

27:43.009 --> 27:46.360
And I didn't tell you
because...

27:46.403 --> 27:49.015
just what if
it's too late?

27:52.366 --> 27:55.151
[ Sighs ]

27:55.195 --> 27:56.500
Listen to me,

27:56.544 --> 28:00.417
whether we have the green light
or the red light

28:00.461 --> 28:05.509
or a purple disco light,

28:05.553 --> 28:08.425
we have each other.

28:08.469 --> 28:10.819
And I need you to know that no
matter what's said in there...

28:12.516 --> 28:15.258
...all that really matters to me
is you.

28:15.302 --> 28:17.521
♪♪

28:17.565 --> 28:18.958
Nurse: Maggie Bloom?

28:20.307 --> 28:21.569
Hi.

28:25.399 --> 28:28.271
Come in with me?

28:28.315 --> 28:30.273
Yes, I will.

28:30.317 --> 28:35.714
♪♪

28:35.757 --> 28:37.063
[ Sighs ]

28:40.370 --> 28:42.155
Nya: There is this armor
that we have to wear

28:42.198 --> 28:43.809
just to get through the day,

28:43.852 --> 28:47.160
and every time another innocent
Black person is killed,

28:47.203 --> 28:49.640
that armor gets
heavier and heavier.

28:49.684 --> 28:54.820
But I've seen what can happen
if we just keep showing up.

28:54.863 --> 28:55.821
Woman: Black Lives!

28:55.864 --> 28:56.822
Crowd: Matter!

28:56.865 --> 28:57.953
Black Lives!

28:57.997 --> 28:59.302
Matter!

28:59.346 --> 29:06.309
♪♪

29:06.353 --> 29:07.920
Nya: Things can change.

29:14.491 --> 29:17.756
[ Cheers and applause ]

29:26.765 --> 29:28.201
Wow.

29:28.244 --> 29:30.159
That was incredible.

29:30.203 --> 29:34.424
This is just the movie
I needed to see.

29:34.468 --> 29:39.560
When Ms. Garnes spoke about
the complexion for rejection,

29:39.603 --> 29:42.041
I felt that in my spirit.

29:42.084 --> 29:46.697
But I just didn't have the words
for it, until now.

29:46.741 --> 29:52.051
It's a kind of weight that I've
been silently dragging with me,

29:52.094 --> 29:56.055
like some inherent
responsibility for being Black.

29:56.098 --> 29:58.013
This weight is our reality,

29:58.057 --> 30:01.277
but with a film like this,

30:01.321 --> 30:04.367
I have hope
things can change.

30:04.411 --> 30:07.066
Please welcome
our special guest,

30:07.109 --> 30:09.546
director Rome Howard.

30:09.590 --> 30:12.114
[ Cheers and applause ]

30:16.423 --> 30:17.772
Rome: Thank you.

30:25.998 --> 30:27.390
I spent a lot of time
thinking about

30:27.434 --> 30:30.698
what I wanted to say today.

30:30.741 --> 30:32.091
Agonizing over the words

30:32.134 --> 30:35.355
that I thought would have
the most impact.

30:35.398 --> 30:37.618
My truth.

30:37.661 --> 30:39.098
And that truth is,

30:39.141 --> 30:42.231
I'm here because of one person.

30:43.754 --> 30:47.062
Someone who was here when
I sat in these very seats.

30:47.106 --> 30:51.284
Someone who's been elevated
to a position of leadership

30:51.327 --> 30:55.592
and has had a profound impact
on my life.

30:55.636 --> 30:56.942
And that person is...

31:00.336 --> 31:03.383
...Vice Principal
Dre Washington.

31:03.426 --> 31:06.516
[ Applause ]

31:06.560 --> 31:10.912
♪♪

31:10.956 --> 31:12.435
Dre not only gave me
the opportunity

31:12.479 --> 31:14.698
to screen my documentary,

31:14.742 --> 31:17.963
but he also gave me a chance
to learn something about change.

31:18.006 --> 31:21.270
Before we can make change
in the world,

31:21.314 --> 31:24.056
we must be willing
to make changes in ourselves.

31:24.099 --> 31:30.801
♪♪

31:33.065 --> 31:34.805
There you are. I've been
looking all over for you.

31:36.677 --> 31:37.721
What's this?

31:39.506 --> 31:41.160
The President's Award.

31:41.203 --> 31:42.683
Hmm.

31:42.726 --> 31:43.945
Is this a bad time to tell you
I have no idea

31:43.989 --> 31:45.164
what the
President's Award is?

31:45.207 --> 31:47.775
I got it our senior year
at the big assembly?

31:47.818 --> 31:50.038
Is this a bad time to tell you
I skipped the assemblies?

31:50.082 --> 31:51.170
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:51.213 --> 31:52.475
Of course you did.

31:52.519 --> 31:54.216
You were too busy
having the time of your life

31:54.260 --> 31:55.696
with Randy and Molly,

31:55.739 --> 31:58.699
while I was trying to be
the model student.

31:58.742 --> 32:02.442
So I could get this.

32:02.485 --> 32:04.748
And you did it.
That's amazing.

32:04.792 --> 32:07.012
My mom was
really proud of me.

32:07.055 --> 32:10.580
You know, to her, it meant
that I'd really been accepted.

32:10.624 --> 32:14.236
I spent four years here, and
I have nothing to show for it.

32:14.280 --> 32:16.238
You're right.

32:16.282 --> 32:18.197
Your thriving law practice
is a total waste.

32:18.240 --> 32:20.199
[ Scoffs ]

32:20.242 --> 32:22.984
Hey.

32:23.028 --> 32:25.987
Everything you are and
everything you've been through,

32:26.031 --> 32:28.381
they're the reasons I've fallen
for you all over again.

32:29.773 --> 32:32.167
That's really sweet.

32:32.211 --> 32:33.952
But I feel like
I can't leave high school

32:33.995 --> 32:36.650
until I do
at least one bad thing.

32:36.693 --> 32:38.608
Okay.

32:38.652 --> 32:39.914
Cover me.

32:39.958 --> 32:41.263
Wait,
what are you doing?

32:41.307 --> 32:42.351
I'm taking this with me.

32:42.395 --> 32:43.613
[ Grunts ]

32:43.657 --> 32:44.571
I don't think
that's a good idea.

32:44.614 --> 32:45.746
Come on!Katherine --

32:48.531 --> 32:51.970
Oh, my God.

32:52.796 --> 32:54.146
Greta: Be careful.

32:55.974 --> 32:58.672
Let's get out of here!
Come on!

33:03.938 --> 33:07.246
Ah.It's a pool party,
and I don't want Milo

33:07.289 --> 33:09.726
and everyone else to see me
with my shirt off.

33:09.770 --> 33:12.164
The guy Milo kissed?
He's totally ripped.

33:12.207 --> 33:14.688
He has, like, a 16-pack,
you know?

33:14.731 --> 33:16.124
And then there's me.

33:16.168 --> 33:17.604
I've been working out
like crazy,

33:17.647 --> 33:20.389
but how can I
possibly compete?

33:20.433 --> 33:22.087
You can't.

33:22.130 --> 33:23.697
When is Gary
getting home?

33:23.740 --> 33:26.482
[ Chuckles ]
Hear me out.

33:26.526 --> 33:28.223
This isn't
a competition.

33:28.267 --> 33:30.269
This is about how you feel
about yourself.

33:30.312 --> 33:32.532
Well, right now, I feel pretty
bad about myself.

33:32.575 --> 33:34.534
Alright, I get that.

33:34.577 --> 33:36.101
And to be honest, I'm going
through something similar

33:36.144 --> 33:38.668
with Anna right now.

33:38.712 --> 33:41.062
But I think what you and I
both need to realize

33:41.106 --> 33:43.108
is that the most attractive
thing in the world

33:43.151 --> 33:44.631
is being comfortable
with who you are.

33:44.674 --> 33:46.328
Oh. Oh, yeah.
Sure.

33:46.372 --> 33:47.895
Easy peasy.

33:47.938 --> 33:49.505
Okay, hold up.

33:52.595 --> 33:54.075
When I look at you,

33:54.119 --> 33:57.165
I see a kid who has
an excellent sense of humor,

33:57.209 --> 34:01.343
who absolutely crushed it
as Danny Zuko in "Grease,"

34:01.387 --> 34:03.084
and who dropped everything
to be there for his mom

34:03.128 --> 34:05.739
when she needed him.

34:05.782 --> 34:09.134
Now, can that other knucklehead
compete with that?

34:09.177 --> 34:10.048
Huh?

34:12.354 --> 34:13.138
[ Exhales sharply ]

34:14.400 --> 34:16.097
I'll go get my suit.

34:19.144 --> 34:20.580
[ Sighs ]

34:20.623 --> 34:24.279
Dr. Anderson: Okay,
see this area right here?

34:24.323 --> 34:26.716
It looks like a spooky game
of wack-a-mole.

34:26.760 --> 34:29.676
[ Chuckles ] Or the, uh,
negative image of Swiss cheese.

34:29.719 --> 34:32.200
[ Chuckles ]
Well, I'm very happy

34:32.244 --> 34:35.160
to report that these are
actually your eggs.

34:35.203 --> 34:36.291
[ Exhales sharply ]

34:36.335 --> 34:39.729
Yeah, and this month,
you have nine.

34:39.773 --> 34:42.080
A perfectly normal count
for your age.

34:42.123 --> 34:43.516
So the party's still raging
in there?

34:43.559 --> 34:44.821
[ Chuckles ] It is.

34:44.865 --> 34:46.301
[ Laughter ]

34:46.345 --> 34:51.263
But when is, um --
when's last call?

34:51.306 --> 34:54.135
From what I'm seeing,
you don't need to rush.

34:54.179 --> 34:55.615
I'd say as long
as you start trying

34:55.658 --> 34:59.314
in the next three to five years,
you'll be fine.

34:59.358 --> 35:00.707
Okay.
Yeah.

35:00.750 --> 35:02.622
If I could give you
one piece of advice...

35:02.665 --> 35:04.189
Sure.

35:04.232 --> 35:06.452
Pressure never helps anyone
get pregnant.

35:06.495 --> 35:09.019
So, start trying
before you have to start trying

35:09.063 --> 35:10.282
so you can just
have some fun.

35:10.325 --> 35:11.457
Did you hear that?

35:11.500 --> 35:13.372
The doc here
is prescribing fun.

35:13.415 --> 35:14.938
[ Chuckles ]

35:14.982 --> 35:18.551
Um, there is just one more thing
I should show you.

35:18.594 --> 35:19.856
Boom!
No way.

35:19.900 --> 35:20.857
Made-Ya-Look![ Exhales sharply ]

35:20.901 --> 35:22.032
Oh!That's not even poss--

35:22.076 --> 35:23.033
I did--

35:23.077 --> 35:24.905
I'm not even mad.
I'm impressed.

35:24.948 --> 35:26.385
You're just --
You're that good.

35:26.428 --> 35:29.214
I know.And you, Doctor,
accomplice.

35:29.257 --> 35:31.085
Did you even go
to medical school?

35:31.129 --> 35:33.043
I promise you,
I'm a real doctor.

35:33.087 --> 35:34.262
Uh-huh.
[ Scoffs ]

35:34.306 --> 35:35.437
After what he just did to me,
he better be.

35:35.481 --> 35:37.352
[ Laughter ]

35:37.396 --> 35:38.919
Mr. Howard.

35:38.962 --> 35:41.182
Congratulations
on the film.

35:41.226 --> 35:43.532
It was impressive.

35:43.576 --> 35:45.186
Thank you.

35:45.230 --> 35:47.971
You know, I'd like to think
in some small way,

35:48.015 --> 35:51.410
I can take some credit
for your success.

35:51.453 --> 35:54.891
You don't get to take credit
for my success.

35:54.935 --> 35:57.503
I succeeded in spite
of this place,

35:57.546 --> 35:58.982
not because of it.

36:01.028 --> 36:02.943
Let me ask you
a question.

36:02.986 --> 36:05.032
My senior year,

36:05.075 --> 36:06.816
what happened
with the water fountain?

36:06.860 --> 36:08.340
I don't know
what you're talking about.

36:08.383 --> 36:10.994
Let me be more clear.

36:11.038 --> 36:14.346
What happened
with the water fountain?

36:14.389 --> 36:19.002
♪♪

36:19.046 --> 36:21.788
The kids should never have
put the sign up.

36:21.831 --> 36:23.877
But that was
a long time ago.

36:23.920 --> 36:25.748
It wasn't just the sign.

36:25.792 --> 36:27.794
It was what you did after.

36:27.837 --> 36:29.317
I tried to help you.

36:29.361 --> 36:30.927
Blowing that incident
out of proportion

36:30.971 --> 36:33.147
would have only put a target
on your back.

36:33.191 --> 36:35.976
Kids pranked each other
all the time back then.

36:36.019 --> 36:37.934
I didn't want you to be
the one singled out

36:37.978 --> 36:39.588
because you couldn't
take a joke.

36:39.632 --> 36:41.460
Nothing about
a "whites only" sign

36:41.503 --> 36:43.679
on a water fountain
is funny.

36:43.723 --> 36:46.334
It's racist.

36:46.378 --> 36:50.817
And you have no idea how hard
you actually made it for me.

36:50.860 --> 36:52.775
It's one thing for a couple
of stupid teenagers

36:52.819 --> 36:54.473
to do what they did,
but it is another thing

36:54.516 --> 36:56.823
for a grown man to tell me
to turn away,

36:56.866 --> 37:00.000
as if that is the way
I should live my life.

37:00.043 --> 37:02.785
As if what they did
wasn't wrong.

37:02.829 --> 37:03.873
I've been fighting
that suggestion

37:03.917 --> 37:05.658
for the last 30 years.

37:05.701 --> 37:07.268
So, any self-celebrating
you do

37:07.312 --> 37:09.792
about how you've made
a difference in kids' lives,

37:09.836 --> 37:12.447
know that you have.

37:12.491 --> 37:14.319
And you should be ashamed
of yourself.

37:14.362 --> 37:20.847
♪♪

37:25.721 --> 37:33.251
♪♪

37:33.294 --> 37:38.647
♪♪

37:38.691 --> 37:40.519
[ Knock on window ]

37:40.562 --> 37:42.216
Hi.
Hey.

37:42.260 --> 37:43.435
Ah.

37:43.478 --> 37:44.523
You look great.

37:44.566 --> 37:45.698
Oh. Thank you.

37:45.741 --> 37:46.916
Thank you.
So do you.

37:46.960 --> 37:48.222
Ah.

37:48.266 --> 37:51.094
I'm really glad
that we're doing this.

37:51.138 --> 37:52.270
You know, to be honest,
I wasn't sure

37:52.313 --> 37:53.706
that you were gonna come
tonight.

37:55.490 --> 37:56.448
[ Sighs ]

37:58.667 --> 38:00.408
No. No, no, no.
No.

38:00.452 --> 38:02.541
It's okay.
[ Chuckles ]

38:02.584 --> 38:06.240
[ Sighs ]I actually wanted to talk
to you about last night.

38:06.284 --> 38:09.548
Look,
ever since my injury,

38:09.591 --> 38:15.380
my, um...functionality
has been different,

38:15.423 --> 38:19.122
and it's something that
I'm still getting used to.

38:19.166 --> 38:21.647
I should have been more
communicative about that.

38:21.690 --> 38:25.303
But I guess in the moment,
I was nervous.

38:25.346 --> 38:27.348
[ Sighs ]

38:27.392 --> 38:31.352
Thank you for saying that,
because, Eddie, I was --

38:31.396 --> 38:32.527
I was really nervous,
too,

38:32.571 --> 38:36.792
and I didn't know
what to say or do.

38:36.836 --> 38:38.272
How could you?

38:38.316 --> 38:40.318
I didn't speak up
because I was embarrassed.

38:42.581 --> 38:45.845
After last night,
I did some research of my own,

38:45.888 --> 38:50.937
and I read that for some guys
with injuries,

38:50.980 --> 38:54.201
it's totally normal
to use...

38:54.244 --> 38:55.681
These?

38:55.724 --> 38:56.856
Those.

38:57.987 --> 39:07.301
♪♪

39:07.345 --> 39:09.390
Maybe we skip
the concert?

39:09.434 --> 39:12.959
♪♪

39:13.002 --> 39:14.221
[ Laughs ]

39:14.264 --> 39:15.831
I cannot believe
after all that,

39:15.875 --> 39:16.919
you almost left this
in the cab.

39:16.963 --> 39:18.051
I know.
I am a hero.

39:18.094 --> 39:19.313
[ Speaks Korean ]

39:19.357 --> 39:20.445
Oh, Mom.

39:20.488 --> 39:22.229
Sorry.
Uh, we lost track of time.

39:22.272 --> 39:23.491
[ Chuckles ]

39:23.535 --> 39:24.536
What is that?

39:24.579 --> 39:26.842
Oh?
This is --

39:26.886 --> 39:28.409
On your wrist.

39:28.453 --> 39:32.674
♪♪

39:32.718 --> 39:34.981
Did shemake you
do that?

39:36.852 --> 39:40.769
Greta didn't make me
do anything, Mom.

39:40.813 --> 39:42.858
Iwanted to do it.

39:42.902 --> 39:46.122
♪♪

39:46.166 --> 39:48.168
And I want to do this,
too.

39:48.211 --> 39:56.524
♪♪

39:56.568 --> 39:59.875
That day, you made an assumption
about me and Frank Harris,

39:59.919 --> 40:01.007
and I let you.

40:02.487 --> 40:04.227
Because I had to.

40:04.271 --> 40:06.229
Well, what do you mean,
"you had to"?

40:06.273 --> 40:08.188
Dad,
just hear her out.

40:10.538 --> 40:14.499
I was going through something
I didn't understand.

40:17.153 --> 40:19.025
When I was a child...

40:19.068 --> 40:23.551
♪♪

40:23.595 --> 40:25.248
...Neil did things to me.

40:26.511 --> 40:27.642
Your brother?

40:27.686 --> 40:29.514
Mm-hmm.

40:29.557 --> 40:33.256
And it lasted
several years,

40:33.300 --> 40:34.736
and I blocked it out.

40:36.608 --> 40:40.481
But it was always
under the surface.

40:40.525 --> 40:43.789
Always there.

40:43.832 --> 40:47.662
And then when he moved back
to town,

40:47.706 --> 40:49.403
it broke something in me.

40:49.447 --> 40:53.276
♪♪

40:53.320 --> 40:54.843
Shelly...

40:56.932 --> 40:58.978
I thought
he was a great guy.

40:59.021 --> 41:01.459
He wasn't, Dad.
He was a monster.

41:03.025 --> 41:07.116
And I-I know that
because he hurt me, too.

41:07.160 --> 41:09.205
What?Ron, I know this is a lot.

41:09.249 --> 41:10.816
No. No, no.

41:10.859 --> 41:12.557
You knew what this man
was capable of

41:12.600 --> 41:14.733
and you let him
around our daughter?Dad, please --

41:14.776 --> 41:17.039
For years, I struggled,

41:17.083 --> 41:19.302
thinking I wasn't there enough
for Regina,

41:19.346 --> 41:21.740
thinking I was
the bad parent.

41:21.783 --> 41:24.264
Turns out,
that was you!

41:24.307 --> 41:25.308
No.

41:25.352 --> 41:31.489
♪♪

41:31.532 --> 41:33.186
[ Door slams ]

41:33.229 --> 41:35.014
Mm.

41:35.057 --> 41:36.842
I'm really -- really digging
your new doctor.

41:36.885 --> 41:38.931
Oh, me, too.

41:38.974 --> 41:41.237
And I am available
to "have fun"

41:41.281 --> 41:42.891
up to three times a day
as needed.

41:42.935 --> 41:43.892
[ Giggles ]

41:43.936 --> 41:44.937
[ Grunts ][ Exhales sharply ]

41:44.980 --> 41:46.416
Please don't ruin this.

41:46.460 --> 41:47.766
Alright.

41:47.809 --> 41:49.071
Mm.

41:49.115 --> 41:50.595
Mm.

41:50.638 --> 41:52.118
[ Sighs ]

41:56.296 --> 41:58.080
What?
You alright?

41:58.124 --> 42:00.518
Uh...

42:00.561 --> 42:02.302
I think I felt a lump.

42:02.345 --> 42:07.916
♪♪

42:07.960 --> 42:09.657
Please say
"made ya look."

42:09.701 --> 42:15.663
♪♪

42:21.321 --> 42:30.591
♪♪

42:30.635 --> 42:40.253
♪♪

42:40.296 --> 42:49.654
♪♪
